# Virtual machines

Widget "Virtual machines" provides management for working with virtual machines in a single view.  

## Instalation

### Set support email

### Version

## Introduction

There is a basic table with virtual machines with several columns. 

 - "ID" with one button. After mouse over there are two icons for easy copying of Virtual machine name and blueprint name
 - "Name" for "Virtual machine" name
 - "OS" for Operation system and its version
 - "IP" for IP address
 - "CPUs" for number of CPUs
 - "RAM (GiB)" - for amount of RAM memory
 - "Azure size" 
 - "Azure location"
 - "Environment"
 - "Actions" - buttons for show/hide advanced information such as Disks, PAM requests and Logs and Actions menu.

 Data disk table
 - "Name"
 - "Disk letter"
 - "LUN"
 - "Disk type"
 - "Disk size (GiB)"
 - "Actions"

 PAM table
 - "Account name"
 - "Role"
 - "Status"
 - "Requestor"
 - "Actions"


## Action buttons / menu items
Actions are functions or tasks that user can do with virtual machines such as "Add disk" etc. Full list of "Actions" is visible under button "Actions". Actions are splitted into three sections:
 - Virtual machines actions
 - Disks actions
 - PAM request actions

User can do only one action on one Virtual machine in the same time. Running actions are distinguided by special loading icon. Action icons can have also different colors
 - red color symbolised error in actions or any other problem
 - orange color symbolised some user requirements, e.g. approval in PAM request

### Virtual machines action list
 - Disks
    - Add disk
    - Add ultra disk
 - Restart VM
 - Resize Windows VM
 - Restart VM
 - Run audit
 - Uninstall (Decommission VM)
    Important note: Uninstall is available only if there is no PAM requests on the VM.


 - Privileged Access
    Contains actions for Approve or reject:
    - Request Windows user account (Windows virtual machine)
    - Request Windows service account (Windows virtual machine)
    - Request sys admin account (Linux virtual machine)
    - Request app admin account (Linux virtual machine). This task is available only for application web server, not for plain operation system VM.

    Important notes: 
    Approve or reject actions can contains breakpoint in the execution. When there is an active breakpoint then user can approve or reject request by actions:
    - Approve or reject

### Disk action list
 - Resize disk
 - Remove disk

### PAM action list
Contains actions for revocation:
 - Revoke service account (Windows virtual machine)
 - Revoke user account (Windows virtual machine)
 - Revoke app admin account (Linux virtual machine)
 - Revoke sys admin account (Linux virtual machine)
